main event: Flashing lights were observed at Seymour Johnson AFB, NC, with erratic movements, potentially misidentified as UFOs.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 5 minutes., Five to six flashing lights were noted in red and white colors., No radar detected any air traffic in the vicinity., Two flights of migrating geese were observed at the same time., The report concluded the lights could possibly be attributed to the geese or environmental factors.
location: Seymour Johnson AFB, North Carolina, USA
witness description: Sgt. and two A2C personnel from the 201 17th Comm Sq (RAPCON)
